    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "the common ground or dwarf hemlock, a bitter, poisonous plant. The Hebrew rosh is rendered “hemlock” in two passages, (Hosea 10:4; Amos 6:12) but elsewhere “gall.” [Gall] (It is possible that the plant is rather the poppy than an hemlock.—Cook.)",
